@startuml
left to right direction

actor "Client"
actor "Consultant"
actor "Admin"

rectangle "Service Booking & Consulting Platform" {
  usecase "Browse Consulting Services" as UC1
  usecase "Request a Booking" as UC2
  usecase "Cancel a Booking" as UC3
  usecase "View Booking History" as UC4
  usecase "Process Payment" as UC5
  usecase "Manage Payment Methods" as UC6
  usecase "View Payment History" as UC7

  usecase "Manage Availability" as UC8
  usecase "Accept or Reject Booking Request" as UC9
  usecase "Complete a Booking" as UC10

  usecase "Approve or Reject Consultant Registration" as UC11
  usecase "Define System Policies" as UC12
  usecase "Configure System Policies" as UC12.1
}

Client --> UC1
Client --> UC2
Client --> UC3
Client --> UC4
Client --> UC5
Client --> UC6
Client --> UC7

Consultant --> UC8
Consultant --> UC9
Consultant --> UC10

Admin --> UC11
Admin --> UC12

UC12 ..> UC12.1 : <<include>>

note right of UC12
Policies can contain:  
• Cancellation rules 
• Pricing strategies 
• Notification settings 
• Refund policies
However, simplified and only one policy for each.
end note

@enduml